(547, 147, 'the_journey_so_far_paragraph_1', '<strong>Pictura Bio’s groundbreaking diagnostic platform</strong> was born out of a unique combination of medical and technical expertise in <strong>virology, biophysics</strong> and <strong>microscopy</strong> from the company’s co-founders, <span>Dr Nicole Robb</span> and <span>Nicolas Shiaelis</span>.'),
(548, 147, '_the_journey_so_far_paragraph_1', 'field_637c73b65ede8'),
(549, 147, 'the_journey_so_far_paragraph_2', 'Nicole, an infectious disease specialist from the University of Warwick with more than 15 years’ experience studying viruses, and her team discovered a new way of universally labelling pathogens so they could be studied in the lab. Nicolas, a PhD student in Biophysics at Oxford University with experience in computer vision and machine learning, combined Nicole’s newly discovered labelling method with a novel pre-processing algorithm and machine learning to detect and identify individual pathogens.\r\n\r\nTogether, they realised that combining these tools and their knowledge had the potential to create a completely new way of detecting pathogens.\r\n\r\nOne of the first people to spot the revolutionary potential of this new technology was Alex Batchelor, now the CEO of Pictura Bio. Alex has decades of experience in the rapid diagnostics space and has previously led an Oxford University spin-out from its earliest days through to a successful split into two new companies.'),
